	<body>
		<form id="ppdExpalanationForm" method="post" runat="server">
			<div class="form">
				<div class="row"><span class="title_1">Explanation of Prompt Pay Discount</span>
				</div>
				<div class="spacer">&nbsp;</div>
				<div class="row">
					<div class="statement">
						<p>
							The Prompt Pay Discount allows you to reduce your monthly bill by $10. You will 
							earn this discount every month when you pay the full amount owed on or before your 
							Due Date. By paying on time, you will earn the prompt pay discount for the 
							following month of service.</p>
						<p>Example:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>
							Your bill is due on Jan 5th for the amount of $50.
							<li>
							Your payment is received on or before Jan 5th in the amount of $50.
							<li>
								Your Total Amount due for next month (Feb 5th) will be $40*, plus taxes and fees</li>
						</ul>
						<p>Beginning with your second month of service, you are eligible to qualify and 
							earn the prompt pay discount. That is when you pay for your second month of 
							service on or before the due date, you will earn the $10 
							discount which will be applied to your third month of service.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</form>
	</body>
